  "summary": "These ESMA guidelines, effective from April 29, 2024, standardize and clarify derivatives reporting obligations under EMIR. They aim to enhance systemic risk monitoring and reduce reporting inefficiencies. The guidelines detail transitional rules, clarify the treatment of intragroup derivatives, explain reporting delegation, and define data quality standards and trade state report construction. They are based on Article 16(1) of ESMA's Regulation and focus on the reporting obligations in Article 9 of EMIR and trade repository duties under Articles 78 and 81.",
